valuate the merits of record-wise and\nsubject-wise data splits under more general statistical dependencies and\ndistributional structures of the data, including situations where\ncross-validation breaks down. We illustrate the application of our tests using\nsynthetic and real data from a Parkinson's disease study.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 8 Dec 2017 15:23:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 6 Jul 2018 23:32:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-10"}
